	   <tr><td colspan=2>These are rarer than chicken lips.<br><br>I was selling idols in EC a few nights ago and was asked if I had one of these.&nbsp;&nbsp;I did not.  Had never even made one.  <br>She was a dark elf enchanter who I believe was named Jemmenai.  (Forgive me Jem if I butchered your name or mess any facts up...feel free to post a correction!)<br>At any rate she had in her posession already imbued stones (she is a chanter/struggling jeweler) that she sold to me so I could actually make the thing.  Further she fell into my employ to enchant some clay. (Thanks btw)  I promptly and happily made the idol and discounted it for the items she had enchanted as well as for the imbued stones.  By the time we were done she paid a whopping 185pp for the idol and I had restocked some supplies and also found some imbued stones that are aggravating to come by.  Very nice ending for both of us.<br><br>The moral of the story and lessons to be learned are:<br><br>She was an EDUCATED buyer.  She knew what her idol was and its stats before she even contacted me.<br><br>She helped obtain the imbued stones.  This is no easy task and to be blunt if she hadn't she would not have an idol right now.<br><br>She was wise to allow me to "hire" her to enchant misc items such as the clay.  She enjoyed a STEEP discount on her product!  (That I gladly granted because not only was I willing to pay any chanter to do the job, I was doubly happy because she was a CUSTOMER as well!<br><br>In the end we scratched each others backs, I made a good friend, and made someone very happy to be one of ... maybe THE ONLY owner of a very rare item!<br><br>This is why I play EQ and why I worked so hard at my trade skill.  Worth it all in the friendship and respect shared between two players.<br><br>Thank you Jemmenai for helping demonstrate how to go about obtaining a first class rare item and to do it with RARE CLASS!  You are one of the few players that ever showed respect for my Trade.<br><br>I learned a lot from you.<br><br>Be Safe All,<br><br>Trafalgar,<br>26th Cleric of Tunare Drinal<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Trafalgar<br>neuroshock@bigfoot.com<br>(NeuroShock)</td></tr>
